rComments: Professor Keymer is a brilliant lecturer. The course material does not make for light reading, however Keymer helped tremendously to add insight, and made the sometimes dry material much more inspiring. He is above all a wonderful person who genuinely cares about his students and the material.
Amazing lecturer! Super knowledgable, interesting and kind! Really digs deep into texts and makes things clear for people to understand.

I took Keymer for granted while I had him, he's so easy going. But now I miss having him as my prof. He's very understanding, kind, funny and easy going. His class was interesting and he's an excellent marker who values creativity. I'm grateful to have had a course with him. One of the best.
One of the very limited number of good professors at UofT.
I love Prof. Keymer. He is so passionate, kind and approachable. He really cares about his students and his studies. Amazing prof, U of T will never deserve him!

Professor Keymer is likely the best professor I've had, and that's out of an extremely strong department at a top university. He always treats students' questions with respect, and makes them very comfortable.  He strikes an ideal balance between looking closely at a text and contextualizing it within a broader intellectual and literary history.
Terrific guy! Super organized, easy to talk to, interesting subject.
